title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.6: NATIONAL CAPACITIES HAS STRENGHTEN FOR SUSTANABLE ACCESS TO Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH)

description.narrative: Basic water services and sanitation facilities are continuously available for children and their families living in areas at risk of food insecurity., which contributes to Climate Change, Disaster Risks And Envionmental Degradation, Reducing Child Poverty, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1. By 2022, newborns, children under-five, adolescents, and pregnant and lactating women, increasingly utilize quality health, nutrition HIV and Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) services and families adopt healthy and hygienic behaviours and practices, including during emergencies.

description.narrative: En 2021, l&39;UNICEF DCO a soutenu la mise en place d&39;infrastructures EHA et la réhabiliter les installations EHA dans les écoles et les centres de santé :5 villages ont bénéficié des systèmes d&39;approvisionnement en eau soit 6000 personnes vulnérables (4000 enfants).179 dispositifs de lavage des mains ont été installés dans les écoles au profit de 35, 800 enfants, dans le cadre de prévention contre le COVID-19.120 écoles et 40 centres de santé ont été effectué une évaluation des besoins EHA,4.000 réfugiés ont bénéficié de l&39;installation de latrines dans le camp de Holl Holl. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/01/2022
